 widely known among the people who only sell and buy stuff every once in a while you would see this sort of thing happen less often. Heck a faq on the trading forum with some of the more widely known scams might not be a bad idea.<br><br>I'm not going to rant about the person that did this because its not worth my time (Kriptonyte if anyone cares). What I did find interesting is my experience with a GM named Pardima. While not expecting much I figured I would report it in the hopes that maybe something can be done. I was told he would look into it but that they couldn't return any items or pp. When I asked why nothing could be done with such a blatant ripoff the response was they have no records of pp trades that don't involve huge amounts of pp (although he couldn't tell me the cutoff at which they have a record). So basically they had no way of knowing how much pp changed hands. I found this interesting because if this is true then this guy can easily move the pp he has scammed from people to other accounts with zero risk of really losing anything. I asked to get the email of the server GM and was told of course there are no GM's for specific servers anymore. All we have now is people who roam from server to server and do nothing. At least with the old system GM's had a rep, they had to deal with a server day in and day out. I will sleep better at night knowing Pardima is on the case though, you know 'looking into it'. What he is looking into I am not sure since there are of course no records. Well again I am being unfair, he can see if anyone else has complained and ban the account that has nothing on it and the guy is out 9.95 for the cd. But again I am not mad at Pardima. I do want to kick my high school guidance counselors ass though. Here is a job where you literally have to do nothing. For every plausible situation there is some obscure line in the EULA that in essence states we don't have to do jack you are SoL. Well I should be a little more fair, <!--EZ